events.info: Approximate Running Times: TBC Prohibited Items: No video, audio or professional photography unless stated otherwise by the promoter. No alcohol or open drink containers can be brought into the venue. Seating in Lounge Rows A-D is strictly NO STANDING. Frontier Touring Terms of Sale can be found at: www.frontiertouring.com/page/terms-of-sale
events.pleaseNote: Children's Policy: All patrons attending this event (including minors/babies) must have a valid full price ticket for entry. Please refer to the venue's website FAQ page for more information on bringing young children & babies. Accessible Seating & Companion Card Holder: Accessible seating can be purchased online. Bookings including a Companion Card ticket can only be collected from the Box Office. The Companion Card must be presented upon collection. Ticket Release Delay - is in place until 9am 27 August. Tickets cannot be sent or downloaded until that time.

accessibility.info:
Please note that accessible seating is for any patron with access needs, it is not restricted to patrons that use wheelchairs. 

Companion Cards:
Companion Cards are accepted for Palais Theatre events.
Your valid Companion Card must be shown to staff on the event night.

Accessible Car Parking:
There are two accessible car parking spaces in Lower Esplanade. 
Access is via Jacka Boulevard through the St Kilda Triangle Car Park.

Guide Dogs:
Guide/support dogs are welcome at the Palais Theatre.

Hearing Loop:
The Palais theatre has a hearing loop available free of charge for patrons with auditory limitations.

Toilets:
Accessible toilets are located on Ground Level and Level 1, next to the venue elevator. 
Ambulant toilet cubicles are in our main toilets.

.

venues.name: Palais Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Box Office is open 30 mins prior to doors on event days only.

venues.parkingDetail: Street parking is available for around the theatre, or patrons may use the car park situated behind the theatre for approximately $5.10* per hour or $12.30* all day, entry via Lower Esplanade. Disabled parking is available at the front of the theatre. *Please check machine as rates may vary
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is available online. If you require assistance with a wheelchair, companion card or special needs booking, please call Ticketmaster's accessible seating line on 1300 446 925 (Mon-Sun, 9:00am to 5:00pm AEDT only). Alternatively, you can submit your accessible booking request via our help page found below. https://help.ticketmaster.com.au/hc/en-au

generalInfo.childRule: Babes in arms are not permitted into the theatre unless they hold a valid ticket for that performance. There are some exceptions, please check the event page on the Palais Theatre website, if unsure.

ticketLimit.info: There is an overall 8 ticket limit for this event.

venues.name: Merriweather Post Pavilion

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: April 1 - Oct. 31 - Mon-Fri 10am-5:30pm at the west box office (in the accessible parking lot) Nov. 2 - March 30 - Mon-Fri 10am-5pm at the admin office Open on show days from 10am (earlier for early shows) until approximately an hour before the end of the show. Open at the main box office (weather permitting) for at least 2 hours on the first day that a new concert goes on sale. Call (410) 715-5550 for further info.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: The customer must have the confirmation # and a photo ID to pick up tickets. Ticketmaster will call may be picked up at any time the box office is open. Signs will be posted in almost all box office windows designating TicketMaster phone Will-Call.

venues.parkingDetail: On-Site and near-by parking is available.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Mobility impairment orders are taken by TicketMaster Visually & Hearing impaired please contact 410-715-5550.

generalInfo.generalRule: No glass bottles, cans, or coolers No outside beverages, except one factory sealed water bottle Personal food items are permitted, as long as they are in a clear disposable plastic bag to display at the gate. Guests may also bring small personal (Tote-type) umbrellas, blankets and binoculars. Low-backed lawn chairs and non-professional cameras are generally permitted, subject to the rules of specific events.
generalInfo.childRule: Children 2 years & older need a ticket.
